## Step 1 ‚Äî Create SSH Key

```bash
ssh-keygen -t rsa -b 4096 -f ~/.ssh/azure_vm -N ""
````

---

## Step 2 ‚Äî Export SSH Public Key for Terraform

```bash
export TF_VAR_ssh_public_key="$(cat ~/.ssh/azure_vm.pub)"
```

---

## Step 3 ‚Äî Provision Azure VM

```bash
terraform init
terraform apply -auto-approve
```

Save the output value:

```
VM_PUBLIC_IP
```

---

## Step 4 ‚Äî Set GitHub Secrets

Go to **GitHub ‚Üí Repo ‚Üí Settings ‚Üí Secrets ‚Üí Actions** and add:

| Name               | Value                                       |
| ------------------ | ------------------------------------------- |
| VM_IP              | Terraform output `VM_PUBLIC_IP`             |
| VM_USER            | azureuser                                   |
| VM_SSH_KEY         | Contents of `~/.ssh/azure_vm` (private key) |
| DOCKER_COMPOSE_YML | Full content of `docker-compose.yml`        |
| NGINX_CONF         | Full content of `nginx.conf`                |

---

## Step 5 ‚Äî Push Code to GitHub

```bash
